# Glossary

The glossary is the indirection layer between flows (which describe
intent only) and capabilities (which carry HTTP detail and the proposed
tool name). When the MCP server is built and tools are renamed, only the
"Proposed tool" column here updates — flow files don't churn.

## Lookup table

| Intent | User phrases | Capability | Proposed tool |
|---|---|---|---|
{{#each intents}}
| [`{{this.intent}}`](#{{this.intent}}) | {{this.phrases_csv}} | [`{{this.capability_anchor}}`]({{this.capability_link}}) | `{{this.proposed_tool}}` |
{{/each}}

## Intent anchors

Each intent below carries an explicit anchor so flow files can link to
`glossary.md#<intent>`.

{{#each intents}}
### {{this.label}} {#{{this.intent}}}

- **Role:** {{this.role}}
- **Capability:** [`{{this.capability_anchor}}`]({{this.capability_link}})
- **Proposed tool:** `{{this.proposed_tool}}` (proposed — no MCP server yet)
- **User phrases:** {{this.phrases_csv}}

{{/each}}

